# Commit Message Conventions

APEX manages branch creation, commit, push, and pull request opening automatically.
The implementation skill must NOT run `git push`, `git commit`, `git checkout -b`, or create PRs.

## Commit message style (informational — APEX commits on your behalf)

When APEX commits the agent's work it uses the conventional commits format:

```
feat(<scope>): <short summary — imperative mood, no period>

Implements APEX-approved design doc for ADO work item #<workItemId>.
- <bullet: what changed>
- <bullet: what changed>
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`, `docs`, `style`, `perf`

## Branch naming (informational — APEX creates the branch)

APEX creates branches as: `feature/apex-<workItemId>-<slug>`

- `<workItemId>` — the assigned ADO work item id
- `<slug>` — kebab-case title derived from the work item title (max ~40 chars)

Example: `feature/apex-42-shift-scheduler-widget`
